pool of the southern Hans. In contrast, northern Hans and southern |XML| xmlLoc_7 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_common xmlPic_no xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
natives contributed almost equally to the southern Hans’ mtDNA |XML| xmlLoc_7 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_common xmlPic_no xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
one-sixth of the southern population at that time) occurred during the Western Jin Dynasty |XML| xmlLoc_3 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_smaller xmlPic_no xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_new bi_xmlPara_new
(AD 265–316); the second migration, more extensive than the first, took place during the |XML| xmlLoc_3 xmlBold_no xmlItalic_no xmlFontSize_smaller xmlPic_no xmlTable_no xmlBullet_no bi_xmlSFBIA_continue bi_xmlPara_continue
